entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An operating system with a focus on AI and automation, aiming to integrate various services and provide a platform for developing AI-powered applications. It is associated with concepts like Eliza Cloud and DAO operations automation.

entities.name: Eliza Cloud
entities.description: A cloud-based service or platform associated with ElizaOS, which includes features like a Video Generation page. It aims to leverage AI for content creation.

entities.name: npm
entities.description: A package manager for the JavaScript programming language. It is used to discover packages of public free code and share your own JavaScript code, or "packages". It has a logo that features a beaver.

entities.name: Eliza agents
entities.description: AI agents or programs developed within the ElizaOS ecosystem, designed for tasks such as automating DAO operations. They are a key component of the ElizaOS platform's functionality.

entities.name: DAO
entities.description: A Decentralized Autonomous Organization. These are organizations represented by rules encoded as a computer program that is transparent, controlled by the organization members, and not influenced by a central government.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A cryptocurrency token associated with the ElizaOS ecosystem. It is subject to price speculation within the community.

entities.name: X (Twitter)
entities.description: A social media platform, formerly known as Twitter, that is experiencing legal challenges with ElizaOS, limiting the project's presence on the platform.

entities.name: cjft
entities.description: A developer and contributor to the ElizaOS project, involved in core development, bug fixes, and preparing for releases. They are also associated with addressing security vulnerabilities.

entities.name: ETH Tokyo
entities.description: An estimated Ethereum conference event that ElizaOS is preparing a workshop for. It is a gathering focused on Ethereum technology and development.

entities.name: Superteam France
entities.description: A French community or organization associated with the Ethereum ecosystem where ElizaOS was presented. It serves as a platform for outreach and engagement within the French tech community.

entities.name: BASE
entities.description: A blockchain network/ecosystem that ElizaOS is potentially collaborating with or being discussed in relation to, possibly through a podcast.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It provides distributed version control and source code management functionality, hosting software development projects.
